<%#
  Top Up Wallet — the FIRST funds modal a logged-in player sees when they try
  to enter a contest and lack funds (the board's no_funding entry blocker,
  selectionBoard#showWalletTopup, plus the chain-layer "no tokens" twin).

  COINBASE-FORWARD (operator 2026-06-13): now that a web2/managed USDC entry
  works (the server signs the on-chain enter_contest with the user's custodial
  key when ENABLE_WEB2_USDC_ENTRY is on), USDC is the cash funding rail again.
  The primary CTA buys USDC with Coinbase (the cdp-ramp buy preflight). There
  are NO entry-token links in the default arrangement; adding tokens or other
  cash rails lives behind the quiet "More ways to add funds" hub (onramp-hub).

  FLAG-AWARE SAFETY (degrade): the kill-switch state (a web2 viewer with
  ENABLE_WEB2_USDC_ENTRY OFF) can NOT pay an entry with USDC, so this modal must
  not pitch "Buy USDC" as their path. The tokenFallback getter (web2 mode AND
  the flag off, read from $store.session) flips the modal to the entry-token
  rail for exactly that audience. web3 and flag-on web2 always see Coinbase.

  The Coinbase rail is server-gated on onramp_rail_visible?(:coinbase) (the same
  policy the hub uses: ENABLE_CDP_RAMP in production) so a flagged-off ramp never
  ships a dead button that swaps to an unregistered cdp-ramp modal.

  One modal id ('wallet-topup'); no internal step machine. Opened by the board's
  funds-needed blocker via $store.modals.open('wallet-topup', {}) on a cold
  board, or swap() mid-flow.

  Modeled on modals/_onramp_hub + _wallet_deposit. CRITICAL: rendered inside a
  host template x-if, so a SINGLE root element. x-data is a double-quoted
  attribute, so single-quote everything inside the Alpine expressions (the
  getters, the x-text balances, the @click swaps). Each inner template x-if also
  wraps a SINGLE root element.
%>
<div x-data="{
       get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} },
       get tokenFallback() { return $store.session.mode === 'web2' && !$store.session.web2UsdcEntry },
       get usdcDisplay() { var c = $store.session.usdcCents; return (c === null || c === undefined) ? '—' : '$' + (c / 100).toFixed(2) }
     }"
     class="relative">

  <%# Top-right close. Backdrop close still works too. %>
  <button @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="absolute top-0 right-0 -mt-2 -mr-2 text-secondary hover:text-heading text-xl leading-none z-10"
          aria-label="Close">&times;</button>

  <div class="text-center pt-1 mb-2">
    <h3 class="text-heading font-bold text-lg leading-tight">Top Up Wallet</h3>
  </div>

  <%# Header balance line. Default: the USDC balance (the funding currency),
      em-dash when the navbar cache is cold. Degrade: the entry-token count for
      the kill-switch (web2 + flag off) audience, who fund with a token. %>
  <p x-show="!tokenFallback" class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4 text-center">
    USDC balance:
    <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-heading" x-text="usdcDisplay"></span>
  </p>
  <p x-show="tokenFallback" class="text-xs text-secondary mb-4 text-center">
    Entry tokens:
    <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-heading"
          x-text="($store.session.tokensAvailable | 0)"></span>
  </p>

  <% if onramp_rail_visible?(:coinbase) %>
    <%# PRIMARY (Coinbase-forward) — Buy USDC with Coinbase. swap() (not open)
        because we are already inside the host, and cdp-ramp is its own modal id.
        Hidden for the tokenFallback (web2 kill-switch) audience, where USDC
        can not fund the entry. border-primary marks it as the primary action. %>
    <template x-if="!tokenFallback">
      <button type="button" data-topup-rail="coinbase"
              @click="$store.modals.swap('cdp-ramp', { flow: 'buy', step: 'preflight' })"
              class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border-2 border-primary bg-inset hover:bg-surface transition text-left">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-white font-extrabold text-lg" style="background-color:#0052FF">C</span>
        <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Buy USDC with Coinbase</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">Card or bank &middot; funds your entry</span>
        </span>
        <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </template>
  <% end %>

  <%# Token-path degrade — reached ONLY by the web2 kill-switch (web2 mode with
      ENABLE_WEB2_USDC_ENTRY off). USDC can not pay that entry, so the entry
      token is the funding rail. Opens the existing tokens-picker step of the
      auth wizard with the props showTokensPanel uses. %>
  <template x-if="tokenFallback">
    <button type="button" data-topup-rail="tokens"
            @click="$store.modals.swap('auth', { step: 'tokens-picker', mintedCount: 0, mintedBalance: 0, errorText: '', redirectUrl: '', txSignature: '' })"
            class="w-full flex items-center gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl border-2 border-primary bg-inset hover:bg-surface transition text-left">
      <span class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center text-xl bg-primary">&#127915;</span>
      <span class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <span class="block text-heading font-semibold text-sm">Buy Entry Tokens</span>
        <span class="block text-xs text-secondary">1 token = 1 contest entry</span>
      </span>
      <svg class="shrink-0 w-4 h-4 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.25 4.5l7.5 7.5-7.5 7.5"/>
      </svg>
    </button>
  </template>

  <%# Quiet link to the Add Funds hub — the other cash rails (PayPal / Venmo /
      Stripe) plus a repeat Coinbase entry. returnModal: 'wallet-topup' tells the
      hub's Back link to slide back HERE rather than to the tokens picker. %>
  <button type="button"
          @click="$store.modals.swap('onramp-hub', { returnModal: 'wallet-topup' })"
          class="block mx-auto mt-4 text-sm text-secondary hover:text-heading transition">
    More ways to add funds &rarr;
  </button>
</div>
